{"title_page": "Hamilton Grammar School", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox school\n| name          = Hamilton Grammar School\n| image         = HamiltonGrammar.jpg\n| caption       = Front of the school\n| motto         = \n| established   = \n| closed        = \n| type          = [[Secondary School]]\n| president     = \n| head_teacher  = Abdullah Altaf\n| chair_label   = \n| chair         = \n| founder       = HTON\n| address       = Auchincampbell Road\n| city          = [[Hamilton, South Lanarkshire|Hamilton]]\n| county        = [[South Lanarkshire]]\n| postcode      = ML3 6PS\n| country       = Scotland\n| coordinates   = {{coord|55.77408|N|4.04625|W|type:edu_region:GB|display=title}}\n| local_authority = [[South Lanarkshire Council]]\n| urn           = \n| ofsted        = \n| staff         = 103.8 {{FTE}}<ref name=\"roll\">[http://www.educationscotland.gov.uk/scottishschoolsonline/schools/hamiltongrammarschoolsouthlanarkshire.asp Hamilton Grammar School \u2013 South Lanarkshire \u2013 Scottish Schools Online 2012/2013] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130703072718/http://www.educationscotland.gov.uk/scottishschoolsonline/schools/hamiltongrammarschoolsouthlanarkshire.asp |date=3 July 2013 }}, Accessed 13 May 2014</ref>\n| enrolment     = 1248<ref name=\"roll\" />\n| gender        = [[Mixed-sex education|Co-educational]]\n| lower_age     = 11\n| upper_age     = 18\n| houses        = Brandon, Clyde, Douglas\n| colours       = Green, Blue {{Color box|Green}}{{Color box|Blue}}\n| publication   = \n| years_taught  = S1-S6\n| accreditation = [[Scottish Qualifications Authority]]\n| website       = {{URL|www.hamilton.s-lanark.sch.uk}}\n}}\n\n'''Hamilton Grammar School''' is a secondary school serving Hamilton, South Lanarkshire.\n\nIt's predecessors can trace their history back to 1452. With the introduction of [[comprehensive school]]s and the abolition of [[selective school]]s such as [[Hamilton Academy]] in the early-1970s, Hamilton Grammar School was formed as a new school, using the buildings of the former Hamilton Academy and the nearby St. John's Grammar School, Hamilton.\n\nThe current Hamilton Grammar building was built in 1913 as the Hamilton Academy building. The building underwent an \u00a38,000,000 improvement in 1995, when the original building was retained and fully renovated, with an additional building extension attached to the rear. The new building contains science and technical facilities. In 2004, a communication development unit was added to the school.\n\nA new Physical Education centre was built at the rear of the school. Building work started in June 2008 and was completed for August 2009. This replaced the old Physical Education department which was at the back of St John's Primary School.\n\nThe current head teacher is Graeme Sives who joined the school on 3 May 2016, replacing the retired Head Teacher, Colin Stewart.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hamilton.s-lanark.sch.uk/head-teacher-appointment |title=Head Teacher Appointment |last1=Stewart |first1=C |last2= |first2= |date=9 March 2016 |website=Hamilton Grammar School |publisher= |access-date= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630105741/http://www.hamilton.s-lanark.sch.uk/head-teacher-appointment |archive-date=30 June 2016 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nA notable former pupil is The Reverend Scott J Brown CBE, formerly Chaplain of the Fleet, Royal Navy who was a pupil from 1980-85.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.ltscotland.org.uk/scottishschoolsonline/schools/hamiltongrammarschoolsouthlanarkshire.asp Hamilton Grammar School's page on Scottish Schools Online]\n* {{Official website|http://www.hamilton.s-lanark.sch.uk/}}\n\n[[Category:Hamilton, South Lanarkshire]]\n[[Category:Secondary schools in South Lanarkshire]]\n[[Category:Grammar schools in Scotland]]\n\n{{Scotland-school-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{